{%- comment -%}
  Anandrasa — robots.txt (production)

  Architecture
  ------------
  1) Render Shopify's default crawl rules first via `robots.default_groups`.
     This emits the platform-managed Disallow list (admin, cart, checkout,
     checkouts, orders, account, password, /search, policies API, etc.) and
     the auto-generated Sitemap reference. Using the default groups keeps
     this file aligned with Shopify platform updates without manual edits.

  2) Append explicit allow blocks for major AI / answer-engine crawlers so
     this store is eligible for Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT Search,
     Perplexity, Claude, Copilot, and DuckAssist. Each agent block ignores
     the `User-agent: *` group per the Robots Exclusion Protocol, so we
     intentionally do not restate the sensitive-route Disallows — those
     routes are server-side protected (login redirects) and the AI bots
     should be able to read every public surface (products, collections,
     pages, blogs, articles).

  3) Do not append extra `Sitemap:` lines after default_groups — Shopify already
     emits the canonical sitemap URL inside those groups; duplicates confuse auditors.

  Design notes
  ------------
  - We do NOT add aggressive Disallow rules for `?sort_by=`, `?filter.`,
    `?variant=`, `?page=`, `?q=` etc. Canonical tags in <head> already
    consolidate those URLs, and overblocking removes legitimate filtered
    collection pages from discovery — costly for both SEO and AI search.
  - Shopify defaults already cover /search; we deliberately do not unblock
    it for AI bots either, because thin predictive search URLs add no
    crawl value.
  - All comments use `#` so they are emitted as valid robots.txt comments;
    Liquid `{%- comment -%}` blocks (like this one) are stripped at render.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- for group in robots.default_groups -%}
  {{- group.user_agent }}
  {%- for rule in group.rules -%}
    {{ rule }}
  {%- endfor -%}

  {%- for sitemap in group.sitemaps -%}
    {{ sitemap }}
  {%- endfor %}

{% endfor -%}

